{
  "stem": "4710.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He was a powerful man.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was called the lager doctor, the lagerarzt.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And also I knew about it, that he's carrying out-- I knew about his-- that he's-- he's-- he's doing medical experiment work somewhere in his-- in the laboratory.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we knew that-- that twins, that was his favorite subject of research.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they had-- they had-- they lived in a separate barracks.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they had somewhat better treatment.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Possibly, they want to keep-- keep them in a better physical condition for his experiments.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And we were envying the twins, that they looked like they were always getting more food.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But at the end of the day, not many of them survived.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I mean, a lot has been written about Mengele-- Mengele's experiments.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I can only say-- I cannot say, only what I heard.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So I-- I just-- it's not really relevant what I-- what I-- what I thought.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And possibly, this is what I know about it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I just read about it later on.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "At that time, we didn't know anything about it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I just knew something that-- something fishy going on with the twins.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We knew-- we knew.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No, we had-- we had-- funny enough, there was always somebody in the camp that knew about-- about Jewishness and knew about the-- when is-- when is the dates.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In fact, my brother had a-- a-- a [NON-ENGLISH], Jewish prayer book for the festivals.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He paid for it a whole bread.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we had a [NON-ENGLISH], one set of [NON-ENGLISH] we had in the camp.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we put on [NON-ENGLISH] every day.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Whenever-- I wouldn't say all the time, but while we had access to the pair of [NON-ENGLISH], there was-- it was queuing up from the early morning till-- till late.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
